36. Fabricio ponte: the bridge (Ponte di quattro Capi) which still exists between the island and the old Campus Martius. It was built (Dion Cass. 37. 45) B.C. 62. An inscription on it says that it was built by ‘L. Fabri- eius, curator viarum.'

37. male re gesta: for the phrase and its correlative ‘bene rem gerere' see infr. v. 74. With this picture cp. Liv. 4. 12 ‘multi ex plebe, spe amissa, . . . capitibus obvolutis se in Tiberim praecipitaverunt.’
